HEADWORD: Conciator
<hw>Con"ci*a`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.
<ets>conciatore</ets>, fr. <ets>conciare</ets> to adjust, dress, fr. L.
<ets>comtus</ets>, p. p. See <er>Compt</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<fld>(Glass Works)</fld> <def>The person who weighs and proportions the
materials to be made into glass, and who works and tempers
them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Concierge</ent>⟦br⟧
